theorem Topology.P3_iInter_closed_finite
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {ι : Type*} [Fintype ι] {F : ι → Set X}
    (hFclosed : ∀ i, IsClosed (F i)) (hFP3 : ∀ i, Topology.P3 (F i)) :
    Topology.P3 (⋂ i, F i) := by
  classical
  -- Each `F i` is open, because it is closed and satisfies `P3`.
  have hOpen_each : ∀ i, IsOpen (F i) := by
    intro i
    exact
      (Topology.P3_closed_iff_isOpen (A := F i) (hFclosed i)).1 (hFP3 i)
  -- The (finite) intersection of open sets is open.
  have hOpen_inter : IsOpen (⋂ i, F i) := isOpen_iInter hOpen_each
  -- The intersection itself is closed.
  have hClosed_inter : IsClosed (⋂ i, F i) := isClosed_iInter hFclosed
  -- Use the characterisation `P3 ↔ isOpen` for closed sets.
  exact
    (Topology.P3_closed_iff_isOpen (A := ⋂ i, F i) hClosed_inter).2
      hOpen_inter

theorem Topology.interiorClosure_iter6_idempotent
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior
      (closure (interior (closure (interior A))))))))) = interior (closure A) := by
  -- First, use the 5-fold idempotence lemma.
  have h :=
    Topology.interiorClosure_iter5_idempotent (A := A)
  -- Apply `interior ∘ closure` to both sides of this equality.
  have h₁ :
      interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior
        (closure (interior (closure (interior A))))))))) =
        interior (closure (interior (closure A))) := by
    simpa using congrArg (fun S : Set X => interior (closure S)) h
  -- Simplify the right-hand side using the basic idempotence lemma.
  have h₂ :
      interior (closure (interior (closure A))) = interior (closure A) :=
    Topology.interiorClosure_idempotent (A := A)
  simpa [h₂] using h₁

theorem Topology.P3_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] :
    Topology.P3 (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  simpa using (Topology.P1_P2_P3_univ (X := X)).2.2
